The paper presents an agent-based negotiation model, which involves coordination and decision-making among agents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Multiagent Systems (cs.MA) category. Additionally, the negotiation model relies on a trusted mediator, which involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The model also involves decision-making and optimization, which suggests that it could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the paper involves empirical evaluation, which suggests that it could belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) category.
